  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "The `pkg/serviceaccount` package has helper functions for reading public and private keys from files. There are similar functions in `client-go/util/cert` we should unify on.\r\n\r\nMissing function in client-go: load an array of public keys from a file or pem blob\r\n\r\nDifferent function in client-go: private key loading apparently is not as accepting as the serviceaccount package. Attempting to use the client-go package led to this error in CI in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/40595:\r\n\r\n> F0201 13:41:21.719814 5 controllermanager.go:167] error running controllers: error reading key for service account token controller: error reading private key file /etc/srv/kubernetes/server.key: no RSA or ECDSA private key PEM block found\r\n\r\nneed to determine which private keys the serviceaccount version can load that the client-go version cannot",
